<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-HefKmd7IHliZvNXb0OkqmQ" name=",_BWumEKM1EeC6tIhMGJuAIA" guid="-HefKmd7IHliZvNXb0OkqmQ" changeDate="2011-08-24T05:22:03.100-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To ensure the compliance of the software safety requirements with the relevant documents, please refer to &quot;Table - 2,&#xD;
    Methods for the verification of requirements&quot;, located in ISO 26262 volume 6, Clause 6.4.8.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This table details various methods for verification of the safety requirements against ASIL level. The techniques&#xD;
    covered are:-&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Informal verification by walk-through&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Informal verification by inspection&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Semi-formal verification&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Formal verification&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It should be noted that Semi-Formal verification of the requirements can be supported by the use of executable models&#xD;
    derived from model based techniques. Semi formal verification is recommended for items with ASIL A and highly&#xD;
    recommended for ASILs B, C and D.&lt;br align=&quot;center&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The verification of the HW-SW interface specification&amp;nbsp;is to be carried out by the persons jointly responsible for&#xD;
    the SW and HW development.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To ensure that the software safety requirements match the system design specification, technical safety requirements and&#xD;
are consistent with the relevant parts of the hardware safety requirements.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
